        <num>CC 575</num>
        <heading>575.  Failure to give security</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 575.  Failure to give security
If the usufructuary does not give security, the court may order that the property be delivered to an administrator appointed in accordance with Articles 3111 through 3113 of the Code of Civil Procedure for administration on behalf of the usufructuary.  The administration terminates if the usufructuary gives security.</p>
        </content>
